Watch Together - MERN Stack Project Requirements Document

Project Name:
Watch Together

Project Goal:
Two users should be able to join the same room, talk through video call, and watch the same video together in sync.

Technology Stack:
Frontend: React (Vite) + Tailwind CSS
Backend: Node.js + Express.js
Database: MongoDB
Real-time Communication: Socket.IO
Video Calling: WebRTC
Authentication: JWT
Cloud Storage: Cloudinary

Core Features:

1. Authentication
- User Registration
- User Login
- JWT Authentication
- User Profile

2. Room System
- Create Room
- Join Room using Room Code
- Leave Room
- Display connected users

3. Video Call
- One-to-one video call using WebRTC
- Camera On/Off
- Microphone Mute/Unmute
- End Call

4. Screen Sharing
- Share screen during the call
- Share browser tab or entire screen
- Stop screen sharing

5. YouTube Watch Party
- Host can paste a YouTube URL
- All users automatically load the same video
- Play, Pause and Seek must stay synchronized using Socket.IO
- New users joining should start at the current timestamp

6. Cloud Video Upload
- Host can upload a local video file
- Upload video to Cloudinary
- Save Cloudinary URL
- Stream the uploaded video to all room members
- Show upload progress

7. Video Synchronization
- Host controls playback
- When host plays the video, everyone sees play
- When host pauses the video, everyone sees pause
- When host seeks to another timestamp, everyone jumps to that timestamp
- Synchronization should use Socket.IO

8. Live Chat
- Real-time chat inside the room
- Show sender name and timestamp
- Emoji support

9. Watch History
- Store watched videos
- Store room history
- Allow users to see previous sessions

Database Collections:
users
rooms
videos
messages
watchHistory

Suggested Development Order:
1. Authentication
2. Room System
3. Socket.IO Setup
4. WebRTC Video Call
5. Chat
6. Screen Sharing
7. YouTube Watch Party
8. Cloudinary Upload
9. Video Synchronization
10. Watch History

Minimum Viable Product (MVP):
- Login/Register
- Create Room
- Join Room
- One-to-one Video Call
- Chat
- Screen Sharing

Final Version:
- YouTube Watch Party
- Cloud Video Upload
- Video Synchronization
- Watch History
- Improved UI/UX

Important Notes:
- Use Cloudinary for uploaded videos.
- Use Socket.IO for all real-time synchronization.
- Use WebRTC for video calling and screen sharing.
- The UI should be responsive for desktop and mobile devices.


